{
  "text": " Running late, so I gotta make this quick. I'm about to meet with more than 400 of the best New Yorkers that money can't buy. Experts on housing, transportation, the arts, labor, and so much more. I've entrusted these people inside with a huge responsibility to provide the policy and personnel recommendations our transition team will use to staff up our City Hall Administration to be ready to deliver on day one. Behind this door are gifted public servants. Artists, heads of nonprofits, organ artists. Some keep the city dreaming, some keep it running, but all of them make it great. We've assembled them into... 17 transition committees, based on subject area expertise. Each committee will be overseen by one of our incredible transition co-chairs. So let's go inside. It's time to get to work.",
